  "text": "For complete orders, Arrow's theorem shows that it is impossible for such properties to coexist [CITATION_1] . We show that this result can be generalized to incomplete orders under certain conditions. This is both disappointing and a little surprising. By moving from complete orders to incomplete orders, we enrich greatly our ability to combine outcomes. As in the example above, we can use incomparability to resolve conflict and thereby not contradict agents. Nevertheless, under the conditions identified here, we still do not escape the reach of Arrow's theorem.",
